Preheat oven to 375ºF. Coat a shallow roasting pan with cooking spray. Season pork all over with salt and black pepper. Transfer pork to prepared pan. In a blender or food processor, combine pears, Dijon and maple syrup. Puree until smooth. Pour mixture all over pork in pan. Roast 25 to 30 minutes, until a meat thermometer reads 140ºF. Let pork rest 10 minutes before slicing crosswise into ½-inch slices. Preheat oven to 375ºF. Coat a shallow roasting pan with cooking spray. Season pork all over with salt and black pepper. Transfer pork to prepared pan. In a blender or food processor, combine pears, Dijon and maple syrup. Puree until smooth. Pour mixture all over pork in pan. Roast 25 to 30 minutes, until a meat thermometer reads 140ºF. Let pork rest 10 minutes before slicing crosswise into ½-inch slices.